{
  "stem": "23090.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And finally, it was-- they hoarded her out, too.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And with that, there was no one else left.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "She was-- she was-- she had to go to a place where the hospital facilities-- as a doctor, to a hospital facility, rather than to a house at that particular juncture.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then everybody, at that point, was supposedly evacuated to go out.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And that was the last place that we were able to stay in the Lodz ghetto before we were-- before we were evacuated, which was 19-- I would say around August of 1944.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Again, I-- I reiterate that the ghetto, to me, was still the last place that-- I wish I could have stayed in the ghetto under those conditions, even worse conditions.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Any conditions, in fact, if I was able to stay there with my family and hold out until the liberation of-- of Lodz, and then make start our lives all over again, in whatever capacity, in whatever fashion or manner.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I say this to you because I say it as a child.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that's all I knew is to be as a child.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And-- and again, I say to you as a child, the most important things in your world to you is your parents, your mother.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And once that was gone, it just became a different ball game altogether.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It just turned me and people like myself into a different human being.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And it just was a-- was another phase, another way of existing.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So the ghetto, to me, still represented the very good thing.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Of all the bad things up to this point, it was a good thing because of being with my family.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were taken out in phases.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Some were-- some-- some went a little earlier.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
